Cleric rez spells and epic effects.<br>
<br>
Current epic is a 96% rez....let's say, for the sake of argument, clerics get a 98% rez as a spell, ordinary refresh and mana usage.<br>
<br>
What cleric in their right mind would use that, over their click stick, after a raid wipe?  And what person would complain about the 2% difference?  I mean, I personally take 90% monk rez's without hesitation when I'm getting dragged over all of the zone to set up a coh chain.  And, yeah, I might notice 3 90% rez'd deaths instead of 96%....and if I were a real monk (not just an honourary monk since I'm usually in the pull group), I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> might</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> start to notice after the 100th death or so, but then, that's the job description.  I'd go xp afterwards, not waste mana or time (remember, not just my time but about 40+ people's time) on 2%.<br>
<br>
What's the point of all of this?  Unless PoP introduces a cleric epic mk2, with a &gt;96% rez clicky effect, no cleric in their right mind would ever get rid of their current epic, even in light of a regular spell with &gt;96% rez.  So arguments that try to claim &quot;Everyone else is banking their epic, why shouldn't we?&quot; aren't necessarily true, as well as essentially irrelevant;  Why should we care what other classes do with their junk?  Care about our own balance, not some &quot;Class00 got a new toy, I want one too!&quot;.<br>
<br>
